# Build context exclusions for `docker build`.
#
# `docker/tutorial/Dockerfile` already cherry-picks the few
# directories it actually needs (lakefile metadata, c_src,
# Sparkle library, docs/tutorial, tutorial-extended) instead of
# running a blanket `COPY .`, so the image build no longer ships
# Sparkle's RTL / firmware / Verilator / IP source trees.  The
# entries below are still useful as defence-in-depth: anything
# matched here is dropped from the *build context* itself, so
# even an accidental `COPY .` in some future Dockerfile won't
# silently bloat the image.

# Lake build artefacts (regenerated by `lake build`).
.lake/

# Tutorial generated artefacts (regenerated by
# `bash docs/tutorial/build-from-md.sh`).
docs/tutorial/Notebooks/Gen/

# Verilator obj_dir trees (re-generated as needed).
verilator/obj_dir/
verilator/obj_dir_notrace/
verilator/*.so

# Editor / OS junk.
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# Local docker volume mounts.
.docker-cache/

# Playwright e2e artefacts (regenerated by `npm install` and the
# Playwright runner — not part of the image build).
tests/e2e/node_modules/
tests/e2e/playwright-report/
tests/e2e/test-results/
